cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.DC, cs.DL, cs.SD

The paper discusses the design and implementation of an active software architecture, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The use of a language for specifying executable architectures suggests a focus on programming languages and compilers (cs.PL). The paper also mentions the use of hyper-code as an underlying representation of system execution, which could fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The use of a decomposition operator and structural reflection suggests a focus on software design and analysis (cs.DL) and software development (cs.SD).
